FBIS4-27523 "dreas106_c_94036" FBIS-EAS-94-106 Daily Report 1 Jun 1994 North Korea Kim Il-song Sends Condolences to Honecker's Widow Kim Il-song Sends Condolences to Honecker's Widow SK0106044994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0409 GMT 1 Jun 94 SK0106044994 Pyongyang KCNA English BFN [Text] Pyongyang, June 1 (KCNA) -- President Kim Il-song of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea Tuesday sent a message of condolence to Margot Honecker, the widow of Erich Honecker, upon the death of her husband. President Kim Il-song expressed deep condolences to Mrs. Honecker and her family and relatives. Recalling that Erich Honecker was invariably faithful to the revolutionary cause of the working class for socialism and peace against imperialism and fascism and actively supported the Korean people in the cause of socialist construction and national reunification, President Kim Il-song said the exploits he performed in his lifetime would remain for ever.
